1 D. F. Any alien who has been denied admission, excluded,
2 deported, or removed, or has departed the United States while an
3 order of exclusion, deportation, or removal is outstanding, and
4 thereafter enters, attempts to enter, or is at any time found in
5 Oklahoma shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a felony and shall be
6 punished in accordance with the provisions set forth in paragraph 2
7 of subsection C B of this section, unless:
8 1. Prior to reembarkation of the alien at a place outside the
9 United States or application by the alien for admission from a
10 foreign contiguous territory, the United States Attorney General has
11 expressly consented to such alien's reapplying for admission; or
12 2. With respect to an alien previously denied admission and
13 removed, such alien established that he or she was not required to
14 obtain such advance consent under this section or any prior statute.
15 E. G. The arresting law enforcement agency shall collect all
16 available identifying information of the person including all
17 fingerprints and any other applicable photographic and biometric
18 data to identify the person. Once obtained, the law enforcement
19 agency shall cross-reference the collected information with:
20 1. All relevant local, state, and federal criminal databases;
21 and
22 2. Federal lists or classifications used to identify a person
23 as a threat or potential threat to national security.
24
