1 The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation shall have the
2 authority to collect and maintain the identifying information
3 collected by law enforcement agencies pursuant to the provisions of
4 this subsection.
5 F. H. It shall be an affirmative defense to prosecution under
6 the provisions of paragraphs 1 and 2 of subsection C B of this
7 section that:
8 1. The federal government has granted the defendant:
9 a. lawful presence in the United States, or
10 b. asylum under Section 1158 of Title 8 of the United
11 States Code; or
12 2. The defendant was approved for benefits under the federal
13 Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program between June 15,
14 2012, and July 16, 2021.
15 G. I. Any person convicted of an offense pursuant to the
16 provisions of this section shall not be eligible for probation or
17 delayed sentencing.
18 H. J. The Legislature finds that the presence of persons who
19 are unauthorized to be present within the State of Oklahoma is a
20 matter of statewide concern. Therefore, the Legislature hereby
21 occupies and preempts the entire field of legislation in this state
22 regarding the presence of persons who have entered and remained in
23 this state without first having obtained the legal authorization to
24 do so. Any municipality or other political subdivision of this
Req. No. 13036 Page 5

1 stat e shall be prohibited from adopting any ordinance, regulation,
2 resolution, rule, or policy that conflicts with the provisions of
3 this act.
4 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
5 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
